<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n54119r"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54119r">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54119r"> 119(r)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Fr. Mathew,</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">They did not know of the existence of grapes but made wine out of fermented grain flavoured with aromatic herbs and frequently drank a great deal too much of it. There were <mark>reformers</mark> who blamed almost all the evils of the time on excessive drinking, and <mark>preached a practical system of temperance</mark> which might stand as a model today. <small> Carl Crow, <a name="CCMK" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CCMK"><cite title="source">Master Kung. The Story of Confucius</cite></a> (Sep 1937) 40</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Fr. Theobald Mathew 1790-1856 was a famous Irish temperance advocate. </mm> </dd></dl>
